James is the tool used to provide the Build/Deploy  informarion of a host querying the Check_mk live status. Provided each host has defined the myrole service.

:- Move these files to these specified locations 

* james - /usr/local/bin
* myrole.conf - /etc/
* myrole - /omd/sites/<nag user>/local/share/check_mk/checks
* check_myrole - on the client machines /usr/lib/check_mk_agent/plugins/ directory

:- Define all your check_mk multisite hosts in jconfig file

Dependancies : 

nc or netcat  - this is an utility that Reads and writes data across network connections using TCP or UDP, install it using yum
argparse - install it using PIP
